data-triple-N3.o: "A census of the population of Australia is taken every five years by the Australian Bureau of Statistics. Censuses were held in 1901, 1911, 1921, 1933, 1947, and 1954, and the five-year period was introduced in 1961. The 2011 census was taken on 9 August 2011. Participation in the census is compulsory."@en
